%3E%26quot%3BDisco%20Dancer%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20%26quot%3BAgneepath%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20been%20active%20in%20both%20cinema%20and%20politics%20in%20recent%20years.%20He%20is%20a%20current%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20the%20upper%20house%20of%20the%20Indian%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENews%20of%20his%20hospitalization%20has%20sent%20shockwaves%20through%20the%20Indian%20film%20industry%2C%20with%20fans%20and%20fellow%20actors%20expressing%20their%20concern%20and%20wishing%20him%20a%20speedy%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20explore%20the%20medical%20emergency%20that%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20hospitalisation%20of%20the%20renowned%20actor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20an%20Ischemic%20Stroke%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20government's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedlineplus.gov%2Fischemicstroke.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMedlinePlus%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20two%20types%20of%20strokes%3A%20ischemic%20and%20hemorrhagic.%20Ischemic%20stroke%20is%20the%20more%20common%20type.%20It%20accounts%20for%20about%2087%25%20of%20all%20strokes.%20It%20is%20usually%20caused%20by%20a%20blood%20clot%20that%20blocks%20or%20plugs%20a%20blood%20vessel%20in%20the%20brain.%20This%20keeps%20blood%20from%20flowing%20to%20the%20brain.%20Within%20minutes%2C%20brain%20cells%20begin%20to%20die.%20Another%20cause%20is%20stenosis%2C%20or%20narrowing%20of%20the%20artery.%20This%20can%20happen%20because%20of%20atherosclerosis%2C%20a%20disease%20in%20which%20plaque%20builds%20up%20inside%20your%20arteries.%20Transient%20ischemic%20attacks%20(TIAs)%20occur%20when%20the%20blood%20supply%20to%20the%20brain%20is%20interrupted%20briefly.%20Having%20a%20TIA%20can%20mean%20you%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20having%20a%20more%20serious%20stroke.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20of%20stroke%20are%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESudden%20numbness%20or%20weakness%