sting%20the%20ministry%20to%20introduce%20the%20Bill%20at%20the%20earliest%2C%20the%20panel%20said%20the%20Bill%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20addressing%20the%20issues%20being%20faced%20by%20the%20cable%20television%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20would%20further%20like%20to%20engage%20in%20constructive%20discussions%20regarding%20the%20proposed%20draft%20legislation%20at%20a%20more%20mature%20stage%20of%20its%20formulation%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Cable%20Television%20Networks%20Regulation%20Act%2C%201995%2C%20by%20bringing%20TV%2C%20OTT%2C%20radio%2C%20cable%2C%20DTH%2C%20IPTV%2C%20and%20HITS%20under%20a%20common%20regulatory%20framework.%20Between%20November%2010%2C%202023%20and%20January%2015%20this%20year%2C%20the%20ministry%20carried%20out%20a%20public%20consultation%20seeking%20comments%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20media%20bodies%20expressed%20consternation%20over%20the%20upcoming%20law.%20Journalist%20bodies%20%E2%80%93%20The%20National%20Alliance%20of%20Journalists%20(NAJ)%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%20(DUJ)%2C%20and%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Working%20Journalists%20Federation%20(APWJF)%20join%20the%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%20India%2C%20(NWMI)%20and%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fgateway-to-censorship-journalist-bodies-express-concern-over-proposed-broadcasting-services-bill%5C%22%3Ehave%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20reservations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20proposed%20law.%20They%20describe%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgateway%20to%20censorship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20joint%20statement%20the%20NAJ%2C%20DUJ%2C%20and%20APWJF%20say%20that%20this%20proposed%20Bill%20is%20a%20step%20further%20%E2%80%9Cto%20expanding%20a%20new%20era%20of%20undeclared%20censorship%E2%80%9D%20and%20increasing%20government%20control%20over%20all%20types%20of%20media%20from%20TV%20channels%2C%20to%20films%2C%20and%20platforms%20like%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video%2C%20YouTube%2C%20radio%2C%20even%20Instagram%20and%20other%20social%20media%20platforms%20as%20well%20as%20news%20websites%20and%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20had%20written%20to%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%20Anurag%20Thakur%20calling%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%5C%22%3Evague%20and%20excessively%20intrusive%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20EGI%2C%20whose%20mandate%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20to%20raise%20standards%20of%20editorial%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20of%20news%20media%20outlets%2C%20had%20told%20the%20minister%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20will%20prove%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20that%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%C2%A0charter%20for%20censorship%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmib.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPublic%2520Notice_0.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Broadcast%20Bill)%20drafted%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20(MIB)%20is%20a%20remarkable%20instrument%E2%80%A6%20this%20is%20an%20omnibus%20set%20of%20rules%20aimed%20at%20shutting%20down%20any%20news%20or%20views%20even%20mildly%20not%20in%20the%20service%20of%20those%20who%20happen%20to%20be%20in%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17075